ğŸ”§ Important Configuration Details:
Port Configuration:
yaml

# Beanstalk expects your app on port 5000
# But your Spring Boot uses 8090

# Solution: Add this to application.properties:
server.port=5000

Or Use Beanstalk Environment Variable:
text

In Beanstalk Console â†’ Configuration â†’ Software:
SERVER_PORT = 5000

ğŸ“ Complete Deployment Checklist:
Before Deployment:

    mvn clean package successful

    JAR file exists in target folder

    Application runs locally on port 8090

    No database dependencies (for now)

During Deployment:

    Choose "Web server environment"

    Select "Single instance (free tier eligible)"

    Upload correct JAR file

    Use meaningful version label

    Wait for green health status

After Deployment:

    Access: http://student-app-prod.eu-west-2.elasticbeanstalk.com

    Check logs in Beanstalk console

    Test all endpoints

